          <Comment>This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individual(s) with ichthyosis (PMID: 18948357, 19863506). This variant is present in population databases (rs398122903, gnomAD 0.007%). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Arg445Glufs*9) in the TGM1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in TGM1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18948357, 19241467). ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 39535). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
